928399891435746", "video": false, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2021018196728479750/OLddmSrT_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Rich \ud83d\udc3a", "username": "heywildrich"}, "content": "@Aquas_Top_Guy i don't really even know.. i assume not. however, this is an extremely hot topic due to how repulsive Vivek is and his Trump / Vance endorsements. \n\nit's kind of setting a tone for the future of the country and i think that's why it's so viral.\n\nliterally 1.5 billion Indians want", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 79}, "images": [{"width": 1206, "heightRatio": 59, "url": "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/HH157LrbUAAT5Sx.jpg", "height": 718}], "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 13, "created": 1778291887000, "id": "2052931086045548693", "video": false, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1800706774024261632/KzpTKBxL_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Crusadergroyperx013", "username": "Crusadergryper"}, "content": "The entire country of India is behind Vivek, this alone should disqualify him from politics for the rest of his life.", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 591}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASsPiZFva", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 27, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8610226, "raw_content": "The \"Rapture\" eschatology is a uniquely American phenomenon that has been popularized due to the fear of fat and lazy American Boomer Christians as they intuit that the winds of the culture are blowing increasingly cold toward them. This silly \"Left Behind\" eschatology had its day during the 1840's and went kind of dormant till the end of the Reagan years. Then white Boomer Christians looked around and realized they had voted themselves into a cultural and ethnic minority in a few years. They adopted the Rapture theology because they hoped to bail out before real persecution starts. It is, in fact, a theology of extreme entitlement. \"Never mind all the persecuted Christians past and present, God is going to swoop us out before it gets bad.\"\n\nDon't be a retard like your coward Boomer grandpa. Gird up your loins like a man, toss his Scofield Bible in the coffin with him, and prepare to be an onward Christian soldier.", "author": "BoricuaPede", "created": 1778420777220, "profile_picture": "jba1ZXmftRor", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "RejectRedditization", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "The Rapture is a heresy for cowards", "last_comment_created": 1778429404935, "content": "<p>The &quot;Rapture&quot; eschatology is a uniquely American phenomenon that has been popularized due to the fear of fat and lazy American Boomer Christians as they intuit that the winds of the culture are blowing increasingly cold toward them. This silly &quot;Left Behind&quot; eschatology had its day during the 1840's and went kind of dormant till the end of the Reagan years. Then white Boomer Christians looked around and realized they had voted themselves into a cultural and ethnic minority in a few years. They adopted the Rapture theology because they hoped to bail out before real persecution starts. It is, in fact, a theology of extreme entitlement. &quot;Never mind all the persecuted Christians past and present, God is going to swoop us out before it gets bad.&quot;</p>\n<p>Don't be a retard like your coward Boomer grandpa. Gird up your loins like a man, toss his Scofield Bible in the coffin with him, and prepare to be an onward Christian soldier.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false,